abstract: Three more European steam-ships arrived yesterday. One of them, the Bath City, from Bristol, had a very long and tempestuous voyage. She sailed on the 13th of November, and from latitude 50 22', and longitude 34 to latitude 44 and longitude 47 , a series of terrific gales succeeded one another. Squalls, of hurricane force, frequently struck her, accompanied by hail, while rain fell in torrents.
